title: Naledi: A Baby Elephant's Tale
description: Scientists and animal keepers fight to save an orphaned baby elephant at a rescue camp in Botswana while struggling to defend its entire species.

title: Nat King Cole: Afraid of the Dark
description: Take an in-depth look at the life and talent of the trailblazing musician who conquered racial barriers to leave an indelible mark on the jazz world.

title: National Bird
description: Three former military operatives offer disturbing, firsthand accounts of the deadly impact that U.S. drone warfare has had on civilians overseas.

title: National Parks Adventure
description: Narrated by Robert Redford, this documentary tours the awe-inspiring landscapes, historic sites and untamed wilderness of America's great parks.

title: Nature: Raising the Dinosaur Giant
description: Sir David Attenborough examines a recently discovered collection of dinosaur fossils. CGI and 3-D scans reveal what the beast may have looked like.

title: Nazi Mega Weapons
description: This documentary series examines Nazi Germany's military hardware, defenses and technology, including fortifications, U-boats and ballistic missiles.

title: Newtown
description: This intimate portrait sheds light on the trauma experienced and strength displayed by those affected by the 2012 massacre in Newtown, Connecticut.

title: Night School
description: Three high school dropouts face a host of challenges when they come back to earn their diplomas at a school with low graduation rates.

title: Nobody Speak: Trials of the Free Press
description: Hulk Hogan's court case against Gawker Media sheds light on wealthy, powerful figures who challenge freedom of the press in order to silence critics.

title: Noma: My Perfect Storm
description: This documentary follows celebrated chef René Redzepi, who has made his Copenhagen restaurant a worldwide destination as he fights to stay at the top.

title: Norman Lear: Just Another Version of You
description: This documentary turns the spotlight on the man behind the iconic "All in the Family," with comments from friends, family and famous collaborators.
actors: Norman Lear, George Clooney, Bill Moyers, John Amos

title: Not Alone
description: An 18-year-old struggling to understand her best friend's suicide talks to teenagers who have grappled with mental illness and suicidal thoughts.

title: NOVA: 15 Years of Terror
description: Officials and experts discuss violent radicalization in the internet age and how governments leverage technology and psychology to address new threats.

title: NOVA: Arctic Ghost Ship
description: Sir John Franklin's search for the Northwest Passage ended in tragedy in 1848. In 2014, a team of scientists sets out to find one of his lost ships.

title: NOVA: Creatures of Light
description: In the darkest depths of the oceans, species generate light to hunt, mate and communicate, while scientists seek ways to harness their power.

title: NOVA: Dawn of Humanity
description: A concealed chamber in South Africa houses hundreds of human remains that may help fill a gap in history and reveal the true origins of our species.

title: NOVA: Himalayan Megaquake
description: A magnitude 7.8 earthquake strikes Nepal in April 2015. Scientists race to calculate the impact and devise ways to mitigate future disasters.

title: NOVA: Inside Einstein's Mind
description: Scientists and experts discuss the brilliant mind of Albert Einstein, whose theories and ideas changed the way humanity views the world.

title: NOVA: Life's Rocky Start
description: The theory that rocks on Earth gave birth to key minerals may inspire people to look at these ho-hum objects with a newfound appreciation.

title: NOVA: Mystery Beneath the Ice
description: Scientists venture onto the ice to find out why krill, creatures crucial to the Antarctic ecosystem, are disappearing at an alarming rate.

title: NOVA: Rise of the Robots
description: Engineers join the race to design cutting-edge robots capable of performing human tasks, but major technical and ethical challenges lie ahead.

title: NOVA: School of the Future
description: Researchers and educators highlight the gaps in the U.S. education system and share their visions for innovative and meaningful learning environments.

title: NOVA: Search for the Super Battery
description: From lithium-ion to flow batteries, host David Pogue delves into innovations in energy storage that could help power a greener future.

title: NOVA: Secret Tunnel Warfare
description: In the thick of World War I, Allied forces attempt the daring feat of planting over a million pounds of explosives beneath enemy lines.

title: NOVA: Secrets of Noah's Ark
description: Historians, boat builders and experts examine the tale of Noah's Ark, studying ancient texts and attempting to rebuild a forerunner of the Ark itself.

title: NOVA: Secrets of the Sky Tombs
description: A team of scientists discovers ancient rock-cut tombs while uncovering how the first settlers of the Himalayas arrived, adapted and lived.

title: NOVA: The Nuclear Option
description: Five years after the nuclear crisis in Fukushima, a new generation of nuclear engineers grapples with the future of this controversial power source.

title: NOVA: Ultimate Cruise Ship
description: An Italian company attempts to build the world's most luxurious cruise ship, but must navigate an ocean of financial and safety concerns to do so.

title: NOVA: Why Trains Crash
description: This NOVA program investigates deadly train accidents and explores how technological advances can help make travel by rail safer and more efficient.

title: Now More Than Ever: The History of Chicago
description: This rockumentary tells the behind-the-scenes story of the Hall-of-Fame band Chicago, from their jazz-rock fusion roots to chart-topping pop hits.
